cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.AI 

This paper is about document ranking in information retrieval systems using a deep neural network approach. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also proposes a Siamese Convolutional Neural Network encoder, which suggests the sub-category cs.CV (Computer Vision) could be relevant. Additionally, the paper uses the RankNet ranking model, which is a machine learning algorithm, indicating the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning) could be relevant. The paper also deals with natural language processing, which suggests the sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language) could be relevant. Finally, the paper uses deep neural networks, which suggests the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) could be relevant.
